OCR

***This program loads an image, recognize characters in it and return***
***text.						             ***


****Instructions****

---Needed libraries---

Opencv - 2.3
Numpy
Tesseract-ocr
pygtk

---In case you dont have them---

#Opencv : on terminal "sudo apt-get install python-opencv"
#Numpy  : on terminal "sudo apt-get install python-numpy"
#Tessereact-ocr : https://code.google.com/p/python-tesseract/wiki/HowToCompilePythonTesseract

---Usage---

1-From terminal run  " python ocrGui.py "
2-Load picture by pressing big button (Located on the left)
3-Browse the picture on images/tested 
3-Press "Get text" button.
4-The result should be visible on the text box on the gui(rigth top side)



Note: "Tested images are located on images/tested/ "

